#: src/tools/mcp.md:3
msgid ""
"ZeroClaw supports the **Model Context Protocol (MCP)**, allowing you to "
"extend the agent's capabilities with external tools and context providers. "
"This guide explains how to register and configure MCP servers."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:7
msgid "MCP servers can be connected via three transport types:"
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:8
msgid ""
"**stdio**: Long-running local processes (e.g., Node.js or Python scripts)."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:9
msgid "**sse**: Remote servers via Server-Sent Events."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:10
msgid "**http**: Simple HTTP POST-based servers."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:14
msgid ""
"MCP servers are configured under `[mcp]` and `[[mcp.servers]]` in "
"`config.toml`. The display `name` (used as the tool prefix "
"`name__tool_name`) is required, plus `transport` (`stdio` | `sse` | `http`) "
"and the transport-specific fields. See the [Config reference](../reference/"
"config.md) for the full field index and defaults."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:16
msgid ""
"Keep `deferred_loading = true` (the default) to load tool schemas on demand "
"— this minimizes initial token overhead."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:18
msgid "Security and Auto-Approval"
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:20
msgid ""
"By default, any tool execution from an MCP server requires manual approval "
"unless your autonomy level is set to `full`."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:22
msgid ""
"To automatically approve tools from a specific MCP server, add its prefix to "
"the `auto_approve` list in the `[autonomy]` section:"
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:24
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[autonomy]\n"
"auto_approve = [\n"
"  \"my_local_tool__read_file\", # Allow specific tool from 'my_local_tool'\n"
"  \"my_remote_tool__get_weather\" # Allow specific tool from "
"'my_remote_tool'\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:32 src/developing/building-docs.md:133
msgid "Tips"
msgstr "ヒント"

#: src/tools/mcp.md:34
msgid ""
"**Tool Filtering**: You can limit which MCP tools are exposed to the LLM "
"using `tool_filter_groups` in your project configuration."
msgstr ""

#: src/tools/mcp.md:35
msgid ""
"**Deferred Loading**: Keeping `deferred_loading = true` reduces the initial "
"token overhead by only sending tool names to the LLM. The agent will fetch "
"the full schema only when it decides to use the tool."
msgstr ""

