#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:1
msgid "Tool Execution Receipts"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:5
msgid ""
"Tool receipts are cryptographic HMAC-SHA256 signatures that prove a tool "
"actually executed. When enabled, every successful tool execution produces a "
"receipt that the LLM cannot forge — because the signing key is ephemeral, "
"per-session, and never exposed to the model."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:7
msgid ""
"This addresses a class of LLM failure where the model claims to have used a "
"tool (or denies having used one) without any independent verification. "
"Receipts create ground truth about what actually ran."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:9
msgid ""
"Based on: Basu, A. (2026). \"Tool Receipts, Not Zero-Knowledge Proofs: "
"Practical Hallucination Detection for AI Agents.\" [arXiv:2603.10060]"
"(https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2603.10060)."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:13
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:15
msgid ""
"Receipts are controlled programmatically via the `ReceiptGenerator` API. The "
"`[agent.tool_receipts]` config section is **not yet wired** — config-driven "
"activation and system-prompt injection are tracked as a follow-up."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:19
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:21
msgid ""
"When the agent loop starts, an ephemeral 256-bit key is generated (never "
"logged, never sent to the LLM)."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:22
msgid "After each successful tool execution, the runtime computes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:26
msgid ""
"The receipt is appended to the tool result as `[receipt: zc-receipt-"
"{timestamp}-{hash}]` before the result is returned to the LLM."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:27
msgid ""
"_(Planned — not yet implemented)_ The system prompt will instruct the LLM to "
"preserve receipts verbatim when referencing tool results. This is tracked "
"alongside config activation in the follow-up."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:29
msgid "Receipt format"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:36
msgid ""
"The `zc-receipt-` prefix distinguishes real receipts from fabricated ones. "
"The LLM cannot compute a valid HMAC because it doesn't know the session key "
"and cannot perform the math."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:40
msgid "What receipts detect"
msgstr ""

