#: src/developing/building-docs.md:57
msgid "How translations stay current"
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:59
msgid ""
"English markdown is the only source maintained by humans. Translations are "
"stored in `docs/book/po/<locale>.po` files, which act as a cache — not as "
"copies of the docs."
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:61
msgid "When English source changes, `just docs-sync` runs two stages:"
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:63
msgid ""
"**Extract**: `mdbook-xgettext` regenerates `po/messages.pot` from the "
"current English source"
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:64
msgid ""
"**Merge**: `msgmerge` updates each locale's `.po` file — new strings get an "
"empty `msgstr \"\"`; changed strings get marked `#, fuzzy` with the old "
"translation preserved as a starting point"
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:66
msgid ""
"Then the script counts fuzzy + untranslated entries. If there's a delta and "
"`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is set, `fill-translations.py` translates only those "
"entries via Claude. **Unchanged strings cost nothing** — the `.po` file "
"cache means re-running against unchanged source is a no-op."
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:68
msgid ""
"Without `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `docs-sync` still runs extract + merge and "
"reports how many entries need translation. Strings without a `msgstr` fall "
"back to English at render time — partial translations are valid."
msgstr ""

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:70
msgid "Adding a new locale"
msgstr "新しいロケールの追加"

#: src/developing/building-docs.md:72
