#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:15
msgid ""
"ZeroClaw routes MQTT/webhook/cron/peripheral events through a unified SOP "
"dispatcher (`dispatch_sop_event`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:17
msgid "Key behaviors:"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:19
msgid ""
"**Consistent trigger matching:** one matcher path for all event sources."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:20
msgid "**Run-start audit:** started runs are persisted via `SopAuditLogger`."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:21
msgid ""
"**Headless safety:** in non-agent-loop contexts, `ExecuteStep` actions are "
"logged as pending (not silently executed)."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:23
msgid "2. MQTT Integration"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:25
msgid "2.1 Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:27
msgid ""
"Configure broker access under `[channels_config.mqtt]` in `config.toml` — "
"see the [Config reference](../config.md). The `use_tls` flag must match the "
"scheme of `broker_url` (`mqtts://` ⇒ `true`, `mqtt://` ⇒ `false`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:29
msgid "2.2 Trigger Definition"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:31
msgid "In `SOP.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:33
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[triggers]]\n"
"type = \"mqtt\"\n"
"topic = \"sensors/alert\"\n"
"condition = \"$.severity >= 2\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:40
msgid ""
"MQTT payload is forwarded into SOP event payload (`event.payload`), then "
"shown in step context."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:42
msgid "3. Webhook Integration"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:44
msgid "3.1 Endpoints"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:46
msgid ""
"**`POST /sop/{*rest}`**: SOP-only endpoint. Returns `404` if no SOP matches. "
"No LLM fallback."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:47
msgid ""
"**`POST /webhook`**: chat endpoint. It attempts SOP dispatch first; if no "
"match, falls back to normal LLM flow."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:49
msgid "Path matching is exact against configured webhook trigger path."
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:53
msgid "Trigger path in SOP: `path = \"/sop/deploy\"`"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:54
msgid "Matching request: `POST /sop/deploy`"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:56
msgid "3.2 Authorization"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:58
msgid "When pairing is enabled (default), provide:"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:60
msgid "`Authorization: Bearer <token>` (from `POST /pair`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:61
msgid ""
"Optional second layer: `X-Webhook-Secret: <secret>` when webhook secret is "
"configured"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:63
msgid "3.3 Idempotency"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:67
msgid "`X-Idempotency-Key: <unique-key>`"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:69
msgid "Defaults:"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:71
msgid "TTL: 300s"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:72
msgid "Duplicate response: `200 OK` with `\"status\": \"duplicate\"`"
msgstr ""

#: src/reference/sop/connectivity.md:74
msgid "Idempotency keys are namespaced per endpoint (`/webhook` vs `/sop/*`)."
msgstr ""

